# ChatEKLD — optional online-provider API keys.
#
# ChatEKLD runs fully offline with Ollama / LM Studio and needs NONE of these.
# They are only required if you route CHAT through an online provider (OpenAI,
# Anthropic, or Google Gemini). Embeddings, indexing, and retrieval always stay
# local, so your notes never leave the machine in bulk even with a key set.
#
# HOW TO USE
#   Dev (running `python launch.py` from a terminal): copy this file to the repo
#   root as `.env`, or just export the vars in your shell profile.
#
#   Packaged .app: a Finder-launched bundle does NOT inherit your shell
#   environment, so keys in ~/.zshrc are invisible to it. Copy this file to:
#       ~/Library/Application Support/ChatEKLD/.env
#   then uncomment and fill in the key(s) you use. A real shell variable always
#   wins over this file (launch.py loads it with override=False).
#
# Keys are read from the environment at call time and are NEVER written to
# config.json or returned by the API.

# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
# GOOGLE_API_KEY=AIza...
